{"lemma":"سَبَلَةٍ","slug":"سَبَلَةٍ","root":"س.ب.ل","root_slug":"س-ب-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ب-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n18811","n18817","n18818"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of سَبِيل (sabīl)","tags":["form-of","plural"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n18811","headword_ar":"سبّلهُ","root":"sbl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tasobiylN","text_ar":"تَسْبِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaEalahu fiY sabiyli A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"جَعَلَهُ فِى سَبِيلِ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He assigned it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the profit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"revenue,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"usufruct, thereof, to be employed in the way,"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cause, of God,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of religion;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the doing of anything,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"all, that God has commanded,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the works whereby one pursues the way that leads to advancement in the favour of God; he dedicated it to pious,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"charitable, uses"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"purposes"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (K, TA;) as though [meaning]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he made it a trodden way"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whereby to advance"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the favour of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sb~l DayoEatahu","text_ar":"سبّل ضَيْعَتَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", using the verb in this sense [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He assigned the profit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"revenue,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"usufruct, of his estate to be employed in the cause of God,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of religion"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to be given to the wayfarer, and the poor, and the warrior against unbelievers, and others."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabiylN","text_ar":"سَبِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sb~l Alt~amarapa","text_ar":"سبّل التَّمَرَةَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He assigned the profit to be employed  in the ways of good works"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the various kinds of pious deeds:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he made the profit to be allowable,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"free, to those for whose benefit the property itself was made unalienable in perpetuity."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA. [See an ex. in the first paragraph of art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hbs","text_ar":"حبس"},{"kind":"text","text":", relating to some palm-trees which 'Omar desired to give in charity.])       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sb~l","text_ar":"سبّل"},{"kind":"text","text":", [either"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sab~ala","text_ar":"سَبَّلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sub~ila","text_ar":"سُبِّلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"both app. allowable, (see the part. ns., below,)]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, long in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabalap","text_ar":"سَبَلَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.];"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as though he had a long"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabalap","text_ar":"سَبَلَة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"given to him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  See also 4."}],"source_refs":["Mgh","Msb"]},{"entry_id":"n18817","headword_ar":"سُبْلَةٌ","root":"sbl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A rain of wide extent."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, O, K.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n18818","headword_ar":"سَبَلَةٌ","root":"sbl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabalN","text_ar":"سَبَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in five places. ―         -b2-  Also (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aArib","text_ar":"شَارِب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mustache"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S:) or the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAy^irap","text_ar":"دَايِرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"small protuberance termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hivorimap","text_ar":"حِثْرِمَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the middle of the upper lip:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hair that is upon"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aArib","text_ar":"شَارِب"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K;) whence the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAlato sabalatuka faquS~ahaA","text_ar":"طَالَتْ سَبَلَتُكَ فَقُصَّهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thy hair of the mustache has become long, therefore clip it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and it is tropical: (TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extremity of that hair:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two mustaches together:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K: *) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is upon the chin, to the extremity of the beard:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fore part of the beard:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what hangs down, of,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from, the fore part of the beard:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj, in his “ Khalk el-Insán: ”) or, accord. to Az, it signifies, with the Arabs, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fore part of the beard, and what hangs down thereof,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"therefrom, upon the breast:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, accord. to IDrd, some of them apply it to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extremity of the beard;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and some, to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hair of the mustache that hangs down on the beard:"},{"kind":"text","text":"in a trad., in which it is said that he [Mohammad] was full in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabalap","text_ar":"سَبَلَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", Az says that it means the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hairs beneath the lower jaw:"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to AZ, it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what appears, of the fore part of the beard, after"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exclusive of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the hair of the side of each cheek and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euvonuwn","text_ar":"عُثْنُون"},{"kind":"text","text":"[here app. meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portion of the beard next the front of the throat"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and what is concealed"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thereof"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA:) or, accord. to Th, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beard altogether:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sibaAlN","text_ar":"سِبَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) [to which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is sometimes added, agreeably with a common license, as appears from an ex. in what follows,] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabalaAtN","text_ar":"سَبَلَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", occurring in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu la*uw sabalaAtK","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ لَذُو سَبَلَاتٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", mentioned by Lh, in which the term"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabalap","text_ar":"سَبَلَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is made to apply to every separate portion [so that the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he has a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabalap","text_ar":"سَبَلَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M.) One says, of enemies,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humo Suhobu","text_ar":"هُمْ صُهْبُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~ibaAli","text_ar":"السِّبَالِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They are red,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reddish, in respect of the mustaches,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Shb","text_ar":"صهب"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And of a man who has come threatening, one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA='a fulaAnN wa qado na$ara sabalatahu","text_ar":"جَا=ءَ فُلَانٌ وَ قَدْ نَشَرَ سَبَلَتَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one came having spread out his mustache,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (K, * TA.) And in a trad. respecting Dhu-th-Thudeiyeh, [see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vdY","text_ar":"ثدى"},{"kind":"text","text":",] it is said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayohi $uEayoraAtN mivolu sibaAlapi Als~in~awori","text_ar":"عَلَيْهِ شُعَيْرَاتٌ مِثْلُ سِبَالَةِ السِّنَّوْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Having upon him small hairs like the whiskers of the cat"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabalapu AlbaEiyri","text_ar":"سَبَلَةُ البَعِيرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part of the camel, in which he is stabbed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stuck, in the uppermost part of the breast;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M;) called also the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tariybap","text_ar":"تَرِيبَة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (T:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the fur that flows down upon that part of the camel."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K. [In the CK,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manoxarih","text_ar":"مَنْخَرِه"},{"kind":"text","text":"is erroneously put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manoHarihi","text_ar":"مَنْحَرِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lataba fiY sabalapi Aln~aAqapi","text_ar":"لَتَبَ فِى سَبَلَةِ النَّاقَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He stabbed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stuck, the she-camel in the part above mentioned:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ltb","text_ar":"لتب"},{"kind":"text","text":": [in the K, in the present art.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kataba","text_ar":"كَتَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is erroneously put, in this phrase, in the place of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lataba","text_ar":"لَتَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) Az heard an Arab of the desert say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"latama fiY sabalapi baEiyrihi","text_ar":"لَتَمَ فِى سَبَلَةِ بَعِيرِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [which means the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lataba","text_ar":"لَتَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] and he supposes the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabalap","text_ar":"سَبَلَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"to be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hairs in the part above mentioned."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baEiyrN Hasanu Als~abalapi","text_ar":"بَعِيرٌ حَسَنُ السَّبَلَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A camel goodly in respect of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the thinness of his skin"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jilodihi","text_ar":"جِلْدِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"): so in the O and K: but accord. to the T,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of his cheek"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xad~ihi","text_ar":"خَدِّهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"); and this is probably the right explanation. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","TA","M","K","T"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}